FBIS4-8805 "dreeu074_y_94001" FBIS-EEU-94-074 Daily Report 15 Apr 1994 YUGOSLAVIA Federal Lilic Chairs Supreme Defense Council Meeting Lilic Chairs Supreme Defense Council Meeting LD1504145894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 1317 GMT 15 Apr 94 LD1504145894 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] Belgrade, 15 Apr (TANJUG) -- A session of the Supreme Defense Council presided over by FRY President Zoran Lilic was held in Belgrade today. As the Yugoslav president's military office has announced, in addition to the members of the Supreme Defense Council, Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic, and Montenegrin President Momir Bulatovic, the session was also attended by FRY Prime Minister Rade Kontic, FRY Defense Minister Pavle Bulatovic, and Colonel General Momcilo Perisic, chief of the General Staff of the Yugoslav Army. The Supreme Defense Council examined the overall military and political situation in the region and the level of combat readiness of the Yugoslav Army and said that the council's decisions have been successfully implemented. Other issues of importance for the defense and security of the country were also discussed at the session today.
